The code as written expects to find all its files in the current
directory. You may change this if you want, by editing paths in defs.h.
Type

    make

to build, and if the build is successful, you can type

    bin/udd

to run the executable.

DATA FILES:
    char.dat
        player characters are saved here. The file as provided contains
        no valid characters, so you will have to create one to start.
    lvl.dat
        Dungeon definitions are kept here. The file as provided contains
        two dungeons, named “Crestwood” and “Squire's Hole”. Crestwood
        is incomplete: levels below the first 3 are empty, and there is no
        Orb.
    not.txt
        A text file to be displayed to the user at game startup.
